Bacsi, caution, many a level head entered here with the same intention, only to be battered down, abused, insulted, and ultimately left in disgust.  The idea you propose, the camp fire, has all to often become a fire fight instead. And yes, I will admit that I shared in that too.<br><br>
Please jump down to a thread at the end, regarding David Hackworth, and read my post.  I think I see common ground there, and a call to arms, for all of us.  I have no &quot;secret&quot; agenda other than to see my country, and my children save, and out of harms way.<br><br>
Frankly, I see several cancers growing on this body called Earth, and I am quite worried. Iran and Iraq to be exact. What does this have to do with Viet Nam? Nothing and everything.  We can waste the rest of our lives fighting the rights and wrongs of the mistaken war, or we can all work together, which is what I believe Hackworth is all about, to save us, our country, our kids, and maybe the planet.<br><br>
I hope we can grow up beyond our collective ego's and loyalties, and evaluate what I have proposed. I don't know enough about &quot;hack&quot; and I am hoping many of you will contribute what you do know, is this the way out, or deeper in?<br><br>
Funny, but not, I can see a day in the future, (shudder) when we all are foxhole buddies against a foreign foe, on our own ground.  I pray that never happens, but I keep my .223 locked and loaded in the meantime, and yes, I was, was, a C.O. once upon a saner time.
